docs.abstract: As a devastating disease afflicts the country’s swine, companies are scrambling to roll out facial and voice recognition and other unproven ways to save them.

docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — China’s leader, Xi Jinping, has offered carrots to President Trump to stop a trade war that has contributed to a sharp slowdown in the Chinese economy. On Tuesday, he also seemed to brandish a stick.

docs.abstract: The company will pay compensation to car owners and civil penalties to federal and state agencies to settle lawsuits over its use of illegal software, people briefed on the case said.
docs.snippet: The company will pay compensation to car owners and civil penalties to federal and state agencies to settle lawsuits over its use of illegal software, people briefed on the case said.
docs.lead_paragraph: Fiat Chrysler Automobiles has agreed to pay nearly $650 million to settle lawsuits over its use of illegal engine-control software on diesel vehicles that produced false results on emissions tests, two people briefed on the matter said Wednesday.

headline.main: Fiat Chrysler Is Expected to Pay Nearly $650 Million in Emissions Case
headline.print_headline: Fiat Chrysler Agrees to Pay Over Rigging of Emissions

docs.abstract: A new law requiring credit bureaus to offer you free freezes applies to children, too. It’s easier than you’d expect, but you may still have questions. Here are some answers.

docs.abstract: Dr. Roberts worked with other engineers to create the underpinnings of the Arpanet, making many crucial decisions. But his work did not make him rich.
docs.snippet: Dr. Roberts worked with other engineers to create the underpinnings of the Arpanet, making many crucial decisions. But his work did not make him rich.
docs.lead_paragraph: In late 1966, a 29-year-old computer scientist drew a series of abstract figures on tracing paper and a quadrille pad. Some resembled a game of cat’s cradle; others looked like heavenly constellations; still others like dress patterns.

headline.main: Lawrence Roberts, Who Helped Design Internet’s Precursor, Dies at 81
headline.print_headline: Lawrence Roberts, Who Helped Design the Precursor to the Internet, Dies at 81

docs.abstract: A former military airfield in Belgium will be used to test technology and help regulators set rules for delivery by unmanned flying devices.
docs.snippet: A former military airfield in Belgium will be used to test technology and help regulators set rules for delivery by unmanned flying devices.
docs.lead_paragraph: LIMBURG, Belgium — Two years after Amazon completed its first delivery by commercial drone, the idea of routinely using unmanned devices to drop off items at front doors remains a distant, if not far-fetched, dream. The recent shutdown of London’s Gatwick Airport, caused by sightings of drones near the runway, underscored the risks and complexities of the efforts.

headline.main: With Drone Deliveries on the Horizon, Europe Moves to Set Ground Rules
headline.print_headline: With Drone Delivery on Horizon, Europe Prepares Ground Rules
